{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The results showed that a time-series technique based on click frequency information successfully identified at risk students with a modest level of prediction accuracy (75%).",
    "The study by Xie (2021) proposed a real-time student performance prediction model based on an Attention-based Multi-layer LSTM.",
    "Every five weeks, the model measured the progress of each online course participant by fusing the clickstream and demographic information from the OULA dataset.",
    "Two classification tasks (binary classification and four-class classification task) were used to test the model.",
    "The model's accuracy has increased for both binary and four-class classification, for binary classifications going from 77.21% at week 5 to 95.58% at week 25, and for four classes classification from 51.89% at week 5 to 66.46% at week 25."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The study by Xie (2021) proposed a real-time student performance prediction model based on an Attention-based Multi-layer LSTM."
  ]
